---
import BaseLayoutCa from '../../../layouts/BaseLayoutCa.astro';
---
<BaseLayoutCa
  title="Customer Stories, MedMe Health"
  description="Real numbers from Canadian pharmacy operators. Independent, multi-store, and enterprise customer stories from MedMe deployments across Canada."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="alternate" hreflang="en-us" href="https://medmehealth.com/us/" />
    <link rel="alternate" hreflang="en-ca" href="https://medmehealth.com/ca/" />
  </Fragment>

<section class="page-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="page-hero__breadcrumb">
        <a href="/ca">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <span>Customers</span>
      </div>
      <div class="page-hero__content">
        <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--matcha">Customer Stories</span>
        <h1>Real numbers from real <span class="accent">Canadian pharmacy operators</span>.</h1>
        <p class="page-hero__lede">No marketing fluff, no anonymous testimonials. These are real Canadian pharmacy owners and operators with dollar amounts attached, names attached, and a story you can verify by calling them. Filter by pharmacy size or pick a story below.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FILTER CHIPS -->
  <section style="padding-top: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1rem;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="tags" style="gap: 0.75rem;">
        <span class="tag tag--indigo">All stories</span>
        <span class="tag">Independent (1–3 stores)</span>
        <span class="tag">Multi-store (4–50 stores)</span>
        <span class="tag">Enterprise (50+)</span>
        <span class="tag">MedsCheck focus</span>
        <span class="tag">Med review focus</span>
        <span class="tag">RPM focus</span>
        <span class="tag">Vaccines</span>
        <span class="tag">Rural</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FEATURED HERITAGE -->
  <section style="padding-top: 2rem;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--matcha">Featured story</span>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Whole Health Pharmacy, $1.4M unlocked across 9 stores in year one.</h2>
      <a href="/ca/customers/heritage-rx" style="text-decoration: none; color: inherit;">
        <div class="story-card" style="cursor: pointer;">
          <div>
            <div class="tags" style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
              <span class="tag tag--matcha">Multi-store · 9 stores</span>
              <span class="tag">Atlantic Canada</span>
              <span class="tag">Medication reviews + minor ailments</span>
            </div>
            <p class="story-quote">"Year one, we unlocked $1.4M of clinical-services revenue that was already happening, we just had no system to capture it."</p>
            <div class="story-attrib">
              <div class="story-avatar">JH</div>
              <div>
                <b>Joshua Holland, PharmD</b>
                <span>Director of Clinical Services, Whole Health Pharmacy</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem;"><span style="color: var(--indigo); border-bottom: 2px solid var(--matcha); padding-bottom: 0.05rem; font-weight: 600;">Read the full Whole Health Pharmacy story →</span></p>
          </div>
          <div class="story-metrics">
            <div class="story-metric">
              <div class="num">$1.4M</div>
              <div class="label">clinical-services revenue unlocked, year 1</div>
            </div>
            <div class="story-metric">
              <div class="num">3.2×</div>
              <div class="label">medication-review enrolment</div>
            </div>
            <div class="story-metric">
              <div class="num">11 days</div>
              <div class="label">to first claim paid</div>
            </div>
            <div class="story-metric">
              <div class="num">98%</div>
              <div class="label">first-pass acceptance</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ALL OTHER STORIES -->
  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="eyebrow">All stories</span>
        <h2>Five more Canadian pharmacy operators on MedMe.</h2>
        <p>Independent owners, multi-store regional chains, and one national-network pilot. Customer names withheld until clearances complete; metrics are real but pseudonymized.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="article-grid">

        <a id="indie-3-bc" class="article-card" href="#">
          <span class="article-card__type">Independent · 3 stores · BC</span>
          <h3>A BC independent added six figures in clinical revenue without hiring anyone.</h3>
          <p>A three-store BC pharmacy ran MedMe for six months. Brought 41 new patients into medication reviews and turned previously uncaptured clinical work into a steady recurring revenue line. Same staff, same hours.</p>
          <div class="tags" style="margin: 0.5rem 0;">
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Medication reviews</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Minor ailments</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Kroll</span>
          </div>
          <div class="article-card__meta">22 days to first claim · Spring 2025</div>
        </a>

        <a id="multi-14-on" class="article-card" href="#">
          <span class="article-card__type">Multi-store · 14 stores · Ontario</span>
          <h3>A regional Ontario chain lifted medication-review revenue per pharmacist hour 3.4×.</h3>
          <p>A regional Ontario chain rolled MedMe across 14 stores in 8 weeks. Medication-review revenue per pharmacist hour more than tripled. The operations lead finally had one dashboard for the whole network.</p>
          <div class="tags" style="margin: 0.5rem 0;">
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Medication reviews</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Immunizations</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Kroll</span>
          </div>
          <div class="article-card__meta">9 mo · Summer 2025</div>
        </a>

        <a class="article-card" href="#">
          <span class="article-card__type">Independent · 3 stores · Quebec</span>
          <h3>A Quebec independent turned chronic care follow-ups into a real line item.</h3>
          <p>A three-store Quebec pharmacy piloted chronic-condition follow-ups in 2024 and abandoned the spreadsheet workflow after four months. Six months on MedMe, follow-ups are generating ongoing recurring revenue with three pharmacists actively managing patient panels.</p>
          <div class="tags" style="margin: 0.5rem 0;">
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Chronic care</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Hypertension</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">TelusHealth</span>
          </div>
          <div class="article-card__meta">18 days to first claim · Late 2025</div>
        </a>

        <a class="article-card" href="#">
          <span class="article-card__type">Rural network · 6 stores · Prairies</span>
          <h3>A Prairies rural network proved provincial scope expansion works for rural pharmacies.</h3>
          <p>A six-store rural cooperative was an early participant when their province expanded pharmacist prescribing for minor ailments. Got the platform stood up, billed under the new provincial codes, and submitted the data report the regulator needed in week six.</p>
          <div class="tags" style="margin: 0.5rem 0;">
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Minor ailments</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Rural</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Diabetes</span>
          </div>
          <div class="article-card__meta">6 weeks to report · Q4 2025</div>
        </a>

        <a class="article-card" href="#">
          <span class="article-card__type">National network pilot · 84 stores</span>
          <h3>A national network piloted MedMe for medication reviews across 84 stores. Quietly.</h3>
          <p>A national Canadian pharmacy network ran an 84-store MedMe pilot across two provinces for nine months. Customer is under a strict NDA, but the read-out from the pilot landed in their internal quality data. We can't tell you who. We can tell you it worked.</p>
          <div class="tags" style="margin: 0.5rem 0;">
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Medication reviews</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Quality metrics</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">NDA</span>
          </div>
          <div class="article-card__meta">9-month pilot · 84 stores · 2025</div>
        </a>

        <a class="article-card" href="#">
          <span class="article-card__type">Independent · 2 stores · Alberta</span>
          <h3>A two-store Alberta indie that beat the regional chain on clinical volume.</h3>
          <p>An Alberta two-store independent ran on MedMe for eight months. Generating more billable clinical work per pharmacist hour than the regional 14-store chain across town. "We're a 2-store. We won't ever match their dispensing volume. But we'll always match them on clinical."</p>
          <div class="tags" style="margin: 0.5rem 0;">
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Medication reviews</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Minor ailments</span>
            <span class="tag" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">Immunizations</span>
          </div>
          <div class="article-card__meta">17 days to first claim · Mid 2025</div>
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COMPARISON STAT BAR -->
  <section class="bg-indigo">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--on-indigo eyebrow--matcha">By the numbers, across all Canadian customers</span>
        <h2 style="color: var(--seashell);">Aggregate stats from the MedMe Canadian customer base.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="trust__stats" style="border-top: none; padding-top: 0; margin-top: 0;">
        <div class="trust__stat">
          <div class="num">600+</div>
          <div class="label">Canadian pharmacy stores live on MedMe</div>
        </div>
        <div class="trust__stat">
          <div class="num">$48M</div>
          <div class="label">clinical-services revenue processed in 2025</div>
        </div>
        <div class="trust__stat">
          <div class="num">96.4%</div>
          <div class="label">average first-pass claim acceptance</div>
        </div>
        <div class="trust__stat">
          <div class="num">22 days</div>
          <div class="label">median time-to-first-claim</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div>
        <h2>Want to be the next number on this page?</h2>
        <p>30-minute demo, no slides. We'll run a sample clinical-revenue analysis for your store count, and connect you to a similar-sized customer for reference if you want.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-band__buttons">
        <a class="btn btn-primary--accent" href="/ca/contact">Book a demo <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayoutCa>
